The government wants people to stay away from political meetings convened by aspirants not in their favour.Meru County Commissioner Wilfred Nyangwanga (above) said no one has a right to disrupt meetings convened by those opposed to them.&ldquo;If you attend such a meeting and you engage in rowdy behaviour, you will be arrested and prosecuted because you could have peacefully stayed away,&rdquo; he said. Speaking during Mashujaa Day celebrations in Meru, Nyangwanga urged residents to respect the right of every aspirant to sell their policies to voters. -&nbsp;